# This file controls whether the toy account is created when starting the Docker Compose stack.
#
# The first time you run `docker compose up`, the toy account (with user and assets) is created
# and this file is deleted, so that the toy account is not re-created on subsequent runs.
#
# If you want to re-create the toy account, you can:
# - Place this file back in this directory, or
# - Run `flexmeasures add toy-account` manually.
